parts.name: CAGp
parts.comment: strong synthetic promoter used to drive high levels of gene expression in mammalian expression vectors. constructed in the lab of Dr Jun-ichi Miyazaki [3][4] from the following sequences: (C) the cytomegalovirus (CMV) early enhancer element + (A) the promoter, the first exon and the first intron of chicken beta-actin gene + (G) the splice acceptor of the rabbit beta-globin gene.

parts.name: CMVp_Tet

parts.name: EF1ap

parts.name: TRE3Gp
